Description
Welcome to our web app. This app helps you explore and shop for various products. You can easily filter products, sort them by price, and switch between different currencies.

Getting Started
Follow these steps to get started:

Clone the Project: Copy the project to your computer.

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/your-repo.git
Navigate to the Project Folder: Open the project directory.

bash
Copy code
cd your-repo
Install Dependencies: Install the necessary tools.

Copy code
npm install
Start the App: Launch the app in your web browser.

sql
Copy code
npm run dev
Explore the App: Open your web browser and visit http://localhost:5173 to explore the app.
Features
View a list of products with details.
Filter products by category.
Sort products by price (low to high, high to low), or random order.
Toggle between Rupee and Dollar currency formats.
Works on both mobile and desktop.
Data
The app uses data from a file called data.json. You can modify this file to customize the product data.

Project Structure
The project follows a typical React structure.

Contributions
If you'd like to contribute to this project, feel free to:

Fork the Repository: Make a copy of the project in your GitHub account.
Create a Branch: Make changes in a separate branch.
Submit a Pull Request: Share your changes for review.
